<dl id="n54135m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54135m">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54135m"> 135(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sloping straight / runes</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <mark>runic</mark> alphabet itself was the invention of an earlier age. It is based chiefly on the old Roman alphabet with such modifications of form and symbol as were necessitated by the different sounds in the Teutonic tongues and by the use of such unyielding materials as wood and stone. <mark>Straight</mark> lines were preferred to curved ones and <mark>sloping</mark> to horizontal. <small> Allen Mawers, <a name="VIK2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VIK2"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a> (1913) 111</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
